# Red Blood Cell Count (RBC)

**Normal Range:**  
4.7 - 6.1 million cells/mcL (men)  
4.1 - 5.1 million cells/mcL (women)

**Clinical Significance:**  
RBCs carry oxygen throughout the body. Low RBC levels may indicate anemia, bleeding, or bone marrow disorders. High RBC levels could indicate dehydration or polycythemia vera.

**Future Diseases:**  
- Iron-deficiency anemia  
- Hemolytic anemia  
- Polycythemia vera  
- Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD)

**Lifestyle Recommendations:**  
- Increase dietary iron intake  
- Avoid smoking  
- Maintain hydration  
- Consult a physician for further evaluation
